cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI 

The paper deals with detecting adversarial examples in automatic speech recognition, which falls under the categories of speech processing (cs.SD) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of machine learning models for speech recognition also falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
